Defendant in custody
Count 1 - Possess fentanyl 2nd + offense - Guilty plea.   
Count 4 - Posses drug paraphernalia - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.   Motion granted.   
Count 1 - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, consecutive to the sentence defendant is presently serving.   Conditions of probation are: 
1) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
4) AODA assessment and follow through; 
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Submit DNA sample.  
Count 4 - Defendant is sentenced to ten (10) days jail, to commence today.  $280.00 court costs imposed to be paid as a condition of probation on count 1.   
